1
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:12,567
<i> Olive, dear!</i>

2
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:13,333
<i> Olive!</i>

3
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:13,867
<i> Mom, calm down.</i>

4
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,000
<i> I'll follow her!</i>

5
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> Officer, Olive got away.</i>

6
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:19,700
<i> Jade followed her.</i>

7
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:20,867
<i> I already called it in.</i>

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,000
<i> Don't worry.</i>

9
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:22,900
<i> Miss Caparas!</i>

10
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:25,433
<i> Officers! Olive is here!</i>

11
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,000
<i> Just cooperate with me.</i>

12
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:29,767
<i>We might be able to convince
Emma to forgive you.</i>

13
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:34,500
<i>No matter who you call, you can
never escape your crimes!</i>

14
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,633
<i> Even if I'm related to Olive,</i>

15
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:38,600
<i>she has committed a crime
against you.</i>

16
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:42,067
<i>I hope my mom will
get better soon.</i>

17
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:45,167
<i>Despite what your mom did
to you,</i>

18
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,767
<i> you still wish her well...</i>

19
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:47,733
<i> Olive, sweetie.</i>

20
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:49,767
<i> Don't lose hope, okay?</i>

21
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,100
<i> Mommy's here now.</i>

22
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:54,633
<i>I will do everything
to help you.</i>

23
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:32,833
Sweetie,

24
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:38,867
I know that I have
a lot of shortcomings.

25
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,667
I won't force you
to forgive me now.

26
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,933
But I will never get tired
of asking for it.

27
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:52,367
Now you're telling me you won't
give up.

28
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,733
Now that you're old.

29
00:01:57,867 --> 00:02:02,967
But when you were still young
and able.

30
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:06,333
You gave up on us.

31
00:02:08,967 --> 00:02:10,933
You abandoned us.

32
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:18,000
I did that because I don't want
you to suffer.

33
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:24,267
I didn't want you to experience
all the pain I've been through.

34
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,833
Perhaps I gave up too soon.

35
00:02:27,967 --> 00:02:34,067
If only I could turn back time,
I wouldn't do the same thing.

36
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:36,933
I regret what I did.

37
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,767
I hope you'll accept me
as your mother.

38
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,733
Even if you can't accept
me today,

39
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:51,400
I'll wait for the next day,

40
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:56,000
months,

41
00:02:58,067 --> 00:02:58,900
one year...

42
00:03:01,167 --> 00:03:02,233
two years...

43
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:05,567
three years...

44
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:06,867
four years...

45
00:03:11,467 --> 00:03:17,000
I'll wait for as long
as it takes.

46
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,933
I want to make it up to you.

47
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:25,933
I want to make amends.

48
00:03:28,233 --> 00:03:38,167
Can you turn back time when you
weren't there for us?

49
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:45,033
From the time that I was in
pain.

50
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,600
When I feel so little.

51
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:58,733
Because I felt like I was
begging my mom and dad for love?

52
00:04:02,233 --> 00:04:12,033
When I kept asking where my real
mom was?

53
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,200
Where were you?

54
00:04:19,033 --> 00:04:26,400
I kept telling myself
before that maybe...

55
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:34,533
Maybe I'll be happy if I'm with
my real mom.

56
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:39,233
Because she'll be proud
of all my achievements.

57
00:04:39,367 --> 00:04:40,967
She'll be proud of me.

58
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,100
I'm sorry, dear.

59
00:04:46,233 --> 00:04:49,100
Why did you abandon us?

60
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:52,633
Why did you let other
people raise us?

61
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:07,300
I love you so much.

62
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:10,333
I love you so much,
please forgive me.

63
00:05:10,467 --> 00:05:12,133
I love you so much.

64
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:21,967
I love you very much.

65
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,400
Oh really?

66
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:30,333
I will do anything for you.

67
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,000
Prove it.

68
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:40,533
What do you want me
to do to prove it?

69
00:05:40,667 --> 00:05:42,667
Do you want me to kneel in front
of you?

70
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,600
I will do it.

71
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:46,233
That's not what
I need from you.

72
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,767
What do you want?

73
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,267
What do you want me to do?

74
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:53,833
Get me out of here?

75
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:55,100
How?

76
00:05:57,767 --> 00:05:59,333
How can I do that?

77
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,433
Talk to Emma.

78
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,767
Tell her to drop the charges
against me.

79
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:18,800
Why aren't you saying anything?

80
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:23,700
Because you love Emma
more than me.

81
00:06:26,867 --> 00:06:28,233
That's not true.

82
00:06:31,567 --> 00:06:33,900
I love you and Emma
the same way.

83
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,200
You and Jane.

84
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:46,533
But you committed a crime
against Emma and Mookie.

85
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:51,567
And you have to pay
for what you did.

86
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,700
So does that mean
you should also pay

87
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:00,067
for what you've done to me?

88
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:04,300
Because you abandoned us.

89
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,233
I want compensation.

90
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:18,100
Pay for your sins.

91
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,867
Make amends for abandoning us!

92
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,133
What now? You can't do it?

93
00:07:30,467 --> 00:07:33,400
It's because you love Emma more
than me.

94
00:07:33,533 --> 00:07:35,000
That's why you keep on choosing
her over me!

95
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:36,600
That's not true.

96
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:41,633
Who am I to you, anyway?

97
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:45,433
I'm the daughter you
treated like garbage,

98
00:07:45,567 --> 00:07:48,567
whom you discarded without
regard.

99
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:54,133
I'm sorry,
I can't do what you asked.

100
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:58,267
I can never forgive you.

101
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,900
I can't accept you as a mother.

102
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:08,633
I am the way I am
because of you!

103
00:08:10,567 --> 00:08:13,667
I end up like this
because of you!

104
00:08:14,767 --> 00:08:17,433
It's your fault, Ligaya!
You did this!

105
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:20,667
This is all your fault!
You are to blame!

106
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:50,600
Dan.

107
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:51,733
Emma?

108
00:08:51,867 --> 00:08:53,833
Go inside with Mookie.

109
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,867
I'm just gonna have
a word with my mom.

110
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,600
Okay.

111
00:08:56,733 --> 00:08:57,700
Come on.

112
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:02,833
Grandmother.

113
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,833
Good evening, Mom.

114
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,400
Wiro told me that you went
to see Olive.

115
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,033
I did.

116
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:28,967
Emma,

117
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,867
I want to apologize.

118
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,300
Why?

119
00:09:37,533 --> 00:09:47,500
I can't be mad at Olive despite
what she has done.

120
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,833
I'm sorry, dear.

121
00:09:56,667 --> 00:10:00,067
It pains me to see her locked up
in jail.

122
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:04,867
Forgive me for feeling this way.

123
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:09,833
Mom, I understand what you're
going through.

124
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:12,600
I already imagine you'll feel
this way.

125
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:26,100
Emma, nothing bad happened
to all of us after all.

126
00:10:26,767 --> 00:10:29,233
Especially Mookie,
she seems fine.

127
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,333
Perhaps we can let this go.

128
00:10:35,767 --> 00:10:38,867
I'm begging you, please.

129
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:43,967
Emma, can you drop the charges
against your sister?

130
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:46,233
Can you do it for me?

131
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:50,167
<i> Kyla!</i>

132
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,733
<i> Damn you both!</i>

133
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:55,667
<i>- You made me look like a fool!
- Ma'am! Please stop!</i>

134
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:59,967
<i>This is why it pains me to
see her suffering,</i>

135
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,133
<i> because she's my daughter.</i>

136
00:11:01,267 --> 00:11:03,400
<i>You got away with stealing
Kyla before,</i>

137
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:04,333
<i>but you're not getting away
with it again!</i>

138
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:06,500
<i> Are you saying that I'm Kyla?</i>

139
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:09,667
<i>You have a birthmark on
your left leg, Mookie.</i>

140
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,667
<i>I can't forget that mark
even though I only had her</i>

141
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,500
<i> for a little while.</i>

142
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:15,433
<i>I'm positive that
you're my daughter.</i>

143
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:17,900
<i> She's lying!</i>

144
00:11:18,033 --> 00:11:20,967
<i> I'm your mother!</i>

145
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:24,667
<i>- No!
- Let her go!</i>

146
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,633
<i> Mookie!</i>

147
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:29,233
Did she tell you to drop
the charges, Mom?

148
00:11:31,367 --> 00:11:32,767
We both know how she is.

149
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:35,867
She just wants to get
in your head.

150
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,867
No, sweetie.

151
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,633
I'm sure she'll change...

152
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:45,200
Once she gets proper mental
help.

153
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,633
Emma, I'm sure that she'll
change.

154
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,400
Think about it.

155
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:51,600
Our family will be together.

156
00:11:51,733 --> 00:11:53,667
We'll be happy, sweetie.

157
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,367
All of you will be together.

158
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:59,300
Jade and Olive are your sisters.

159
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:02,133
I want to make amends.

160
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:08,167
When I gave them up,
Jade became ill, and Olive too.

161
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:11,067
They both suffer.

162
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,600
But Olive suffered the most.

163
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,300
That's why I'm begging you,
please.

164
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,267
Why are you only thinking about
Olive?

165
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:33,000
Didn't you remember how I
suffered when I lost Kyla?

166
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:36,400
What Mookie went through
with Olive.

167
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:38,033
Did you forget about that?

168
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,567
No, Emma.

169
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,300
That's not true.

170
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,800
You don't understand.

171
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:45,333
Mom!

172
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,300
That's not true.

173
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:47,767
Mom!

174
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:51,733
Mookie suffered so much in
Olive's hands.

175
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:54,400
And I wasn't there
to protect her.

176
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:59,067
I understand what you're going
through.

177
00:13:00,133 --> 00:13:02,100
Forgive me, Mom,

178
00:13:03,567 --> 00:13:06,733
because I can't forgive her for
what she's done to my daughter.

179
00:13:10,467 --> 00:13:13,967
- Goodnight.
- Emma. Emma, dear.

180
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:18,667
Please. I'm begging you.

181
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:55,667
Can someone let me use their
cellphone?

182
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:59,200
I need to call my lawyer.
It's my right to do so!

183
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,033
Hello!

184
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:02,233
I need a cellphone.

185
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:04,967
Can you just please give me
a cellphone now?

186
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:06,133
Hey!

187
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:07,700
Are you going to ignore me?

188
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:10,200
Excuse me.

189
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:14,500
Finally.

190
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:16,400
I told you to wait, Caparas!

191
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,633
Finally you...

192
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:34,033
What are you doing here?

193
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:37,033
Can't I visit my daughter's
kidnapper?

194
00:14:41,067 --> 00:14:42,933
Are you enjoying
your new throne?

195
00:14:43,567 --> 00:14:44,300
You like this jail?

196
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:47,900
Is that why you came here?

197
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:49,367
To gloat?

198
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:51,567
To insult me?

199
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:57,633
I'm sorry, but you'll never see
me defeated.

200
00:14:57,767 --> 00:15:01,700
Astrid and my lawyer are on
their way here to bail me out.

201
00:15:03,467 --> 00:15:05,467
Do you think they'll let you out
on bail?

202
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:07,967
Perhaps you can,

203
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,067
but based on what I heard,

204
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,633
you won't be able
to process your papers now

205
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:15,000
cause it's the weekend.

206
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:17,200
And according to that officer,

207
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:21,300
you might not be able
to get out on bail.

208
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:22,233
No!

209
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:25,333
I have money.

210
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:27,567
I can pay for anything.

211
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:29,033
I can even buy you!

212
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:31,133
You're unbelievable!

213
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:33,700
Do you think you can get away
from all the charges

214
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:35,467
against you?

215
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:37,367
Is that why you're trying
to use my mom?

216
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,267
To convince me to drop
all charges against you?

217
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,900
I don't know what you're talking
about.

218
00:15:45,133 --> 00:15:48,467
I know your evil ways.

219
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,267
You'll use Mom.

220
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,733
For what?

221
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:54,400
To get away from your crimes.

222
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:55,533
And then what?

223
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:57,233
You'll leave her hanging?

224
00:15:57,367 --> 00:15:59,033
You're going to hurt her.

225
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:01,100
Because you don't love her.

226
00:16:01,233 --> 00:16:02,633
Why would I love her?

227
00:16:03,933 --> 00:16:06,433
Didn't she abandon me?

228
00:16:06,567 --> 00:16:08,700
I will never forgive her.

229
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:12,233
I will never forget
what she did!

230
00:16:12,367 --> 00:16:14,600
So we feel the same way.

231
00:16:16,133 --> 00:16:17,600
You were a mother, too.

232
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:22,667
But you're not like our mom,
who gave up her children.

233
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:24,900
I will never do that!

234
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:27,800
But you made her life miserable!

235
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:33,667
So what makes you different?

236
00:16:34,767 --> 00:16:38,067
Our mom gave you up to give you
a better life.

237
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:40,167
What about Mookie?

238
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,800
You had her,
but you tortured her!

239
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:45,500
You made Mookie's life
miserable.

240
00:16:45,633 --> 00:16:48,467
That's why I can
never forgive you!

241
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,300
You can rot in jail!

242
00:16:50,433 --> 00:16:51,933
Get out of here!

243
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:54,833
I don't ever want to see you!
Get out!

244
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:56,533
Don't worry.

245
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:59,067
You won't see me again.

246
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:02,133
Because you will rot in here!

247
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:11,133
Did Emma tell you that
she's going to see Olive?

248
00:17:12,767 --> 00:17:13,800
Yes, she did.

249
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:19,733
We offered to go with her.
But she wants to go by herself.

250
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:24,067
You shouldn't have let her go
alone.

251
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,400
What if something happened?

252
00:17:29,067 --> 00:17:33,433
Perhaps she just wants
to talk to Olive.

253
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:38,333
They might reconcile.

254
00:17:42,033 --> 00:17:44,300
I don't think so.

255
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,233
She looks like she's ready
to pounce.

256
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,433
Barking Like that.

257
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:52,900
Knock it off.

258
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:02,433
You monster! You annoying brat!
You're pissing me off!

259
00:18:02,567 --> 00:18:05,733
When I get out of here,
I'll get you first! You'll see!

260
00:18:06,767 --> 00:18:08,800
Don't you want to stay here?

261
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:11,533
You're the most vile person
here.

262
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:15,600
You can make them your
followers if you want.

263
00:18:15,733 --> 00:18:19,400
You can play as a Queen
or a Doctor.

264
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,733
I'm not sure if they'll want
to be your patient, though.

265
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:24,467
You monster!

266
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:28,567
I'll get you the moment
I get out of here.

267
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,933
I hate you!

268
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,800
I hate you!

269
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:35,667
Hey, shut up! You're so loud!
You're disturbing our peace!

270
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,767
You know what, this woman looks
familiar.

271
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:43,233
Before I got detained,
I saw her in a viral video.

272
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:44,567
That's not true.

273
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:45,900
That's true!

274
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:47,233
I remember her.

275
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:49,367
She kidnapped Emma's daughter.

276
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,900
She's a kidnapper!

277
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:52,433
I'm not a kidnapper!

278
00:18:52,567 --> 00:18:55,633
Don't believe that woman!
I'm not a kidnapper.

279
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,200
Oh, so you're a kidnapper!

280
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:58,433
Come here, I'll give you a fair
fight!

281
00:18:59,367 --> 00:19:00,667
Let me go!

282
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:04,733
Get her!

283
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:15,200
Let me see how tough you
are now!

284
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:25,300
- Come on! Fight me!
- What now! Fight! Get her!

285
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:29,567
Help! Help me!

286
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:36,333
So you think you're tough?
What now? Come on! Get up!

287
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:42,000
- Fight me! Get up!
- Come on! Get up!

288
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:43,933
See, you're not tough!

289
00:19:44,067 --> 00:19:46,867
You're nothing, weakling!

290
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,067
You can't even fight!

291
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:53,400
You're all talk,
but you're a weakling!

292
00:19:53,533 --> 00:19:54,733
Look at her now.

293
00:19:54,867 --> 00:19:56,167
She's nothing.

294
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:18,700
Emma.

295
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:22,200
Come here, sit down.

296
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,833
We're about to follow you
to the precinct.

297
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,733
You shouldn't have gone there.

298
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:32,400
I'm sorry, I can't stand
what Olive did to Mookie.

299
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:37,200
And she's using my mom
to make me drop the charges.

300
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:43,033
And my mom thinks Olive will
accept her.

301
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:44,833
Olive is just using her.

302
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:50,500
Okay, don't ever go there again.

303
00:20:50,633 --> 00:20:52,433
You might get hurt.

304
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:57,400
Let the law punish her.

305
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:00,167
Okay?

306
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:18,000
You have to wait for these
criminals to bully me

307
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:19,533
before you come here?

308
00:21:19,667 --> 00:21:20,733
Sorry, Olive.

309
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:23,533
I'm afraid the officers
might try to arrest me, too.

310
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:28,400
I also heard that Emma
is your sister.

311
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:31,233
Can't you reconcile with them?

312
00:21:31,367 --> 00:21:33,000
She's your sister anyway.

313
00:21:33,133 --> 00:21:36,667
Please, I don't want to talk
about that.

314
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,833
Attorney, what can you do
for me?

315
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:40,300
How can you get me out of here?

316
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:41,800
I'm sorry, Miss Caparas,

317
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:45,833
but the charges against you
are non-bailable.

318
00:21:45,967 --> 00:21:48,833
Due to the severity
of these accusations.

319
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:50,000
What?

320
00:21:50,133 --> 00:21:53,700
However, we're exploring
possible legal strategies.

321
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,700
Astrid and I talked about it.

322
00:21:56,833 --> 00:22:00,067
We've come up with a defense
to get you out of jail.

323
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,767
What is it?

324
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:04,767
Astrid told me about your
condition.

325
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:08,867
The Munchausen syndrome
by proxy, or MSBP.

326
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,433
We're considering this
as a potential defense.

327
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:13,200
To get you out of jail.

328
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:16,300
She told me that we can
use your condition

329
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:20,800
to establish grounds
for a plea of insanity.

330
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:22,100
What?

331
00:22:22,233 --> 00:22:26,133
You want to tell them
that I'm crazy?

332
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,267
I'm not crazy!

333
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:35,200
Olive, we have no other options.

334
00:22:39,467 --> 00:22:40,067
Fine,

335
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,667
if you're going to use
that excuse.

336
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:44,900
Will I be free?

337
00:22:45,033 --> 00:22:46,500
Can you get me out of here?

338
00:22:46,633 --> 00:22:50,633
You'll be transferred
to a mental health institution.

339
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,367
That's the same!

340
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:54,067
I will still be locked up!

341
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:56,767
I want to be out of here!

342
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:59,400
I want to be free.
I want to see Mookie.

343
00:23:00,533 --> 00:23:03,600
Olive, that's all we can do
for now.

344
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,767
The lawyer's been here.

345
00:23:22,933 --> 00:23:24,667
The arraignment is about
to start.

346
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,433
Be honest with me, Astrid.

347
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:31,800
Do I have a chance
to get Mookie back?

348
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,300
I don't know.

349
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:37,633
But with all the charges
stacked against you.

350
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:39,667
I don't think it's possible.

351
00:23:40,867 --> 00:23:43,567
I can't bear to lose Mookie.

352
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:48,600
Olive! Olive!

353
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:51,700
Come on! Don't even try to get
near me!

354
00:23:51,833 --> 00:23:53,700
I will blow her head up!

355
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:54,567
Olive!

356
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:00,833
We're twins.

357
00:24:00,967 --> 00:24:05,167
It means we're connected.

358
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:09,900
We'll leave this world behind
together.

359
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,667
Dan, we're gonna crash!

360
00:24:13,967 --> 00:24:15,867
I have a feeling that something
bad is happening.

361
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:19,233
I don't know what's going on,
but I feel something is wrong.

362
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:20,833
You're a meddler!

363
00:24:20,967 --> 00:24:21,867
Let me go!

364
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,600
Olive!
